<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06078176 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06078176 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  TELEPHONE; ADVERTISING; HUMOR  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  It's not enough that Gary Gleason phones his mother. Lately, he's had everyonein town doing it.;    Gleason, marketing director for the Roaring Fork TransitAgency, thought a banner fluttering over Main Street promoting the company'sbus service and offering its phone number would mean increased interest in theservice.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  General News  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  OOPS, IF A MOM ANSWERS, JUST HANG UP PHONE  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     But it has meant many increased phone calls to Gleason's mother, Mary.That's because the 2-foot-high phone number on the banner is her's, not thetransit agency's.;    &quot;When I was writing the copy for the banner, I wrote thephone number I thought was the right one at the time,&quot; Gleason said.;   Gleason learned of the mistake when his mother called shortly after the bannerwent up last week.;    &quot;She said, 'Gary, do you realize what's happened?' &quot;Gleason said.;    The banner with the wrong number was to come down today.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Associated Press  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><CITY>  Aspen, Colo.  </CITY><EDITION>  Stock Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910318  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Monday  </DAY><MONTH>  March  </MONTH><PG.COL>  56D  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  143  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Monday March 18, 199100078176,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>